articles.author: Lee Ying Shan
articles.title: Asia-Pacific markets trade mixed as investors await U.S. election outcome, Fed rate verdict - CNBC
articles.description: Asia-Pacific markets traded mixed on Tuesday as investors prepared for a possible interest rate cut from the Federal Reserve later this week.
articles.content:
Traders are still pricing in Federal Reserve rate cuts too aggressively, according to the BlackRock Investment Institute.
